segment.source: Extract Files from a Compressed USMT Migration Store
segment.target: Extract Files from a Compressed USMT Migration Store

segment.source: When you migrate files and settings during a typical PC-refresh migration, you usually create a compressed migration store file on the intermediate store.
segment.target: When you migrate files and settings during a typical PC-refresh migration, you usually create a compressed migration store file on the intermediate store.

segment.source: This migration store is a single image file that contains all files being migrated as well as a catalog file.
segment.target: This migration store is a single image file that contains all files being migrated as well as a catalog file.

segment.source: To protect the compressed file, you can encrypt it by using different encryption algorithms.
segment.target: To protect the compressed file, you can encrypt it by using different encryption algorithms.

segment.source: When you migrate the file back to the source computer after the operating system is installed, you can run the Usmtutils command with the /extract option to recover the files from the compressed migration store.
segment.target: When you migrate the file back to the source computer after the operating system is installed, you can run the Usmtutils command with the /extract option to recover the files from the compressed migration store.

segment.source: You can also use the Usmtutils command with the /extract option any time you need to recover data from a migration store.
segment.target: You can also use the Usmtutils command with the /extract option any time you need to recover data from a migration store.

segment.source: Options used with the /extract option can specify:
segment.target: Options used with the /extract option can specify:

segment.source: The cryptographic algorithm that was used to create the migration store.
segment.target: The cryptographic algorithm that was used to create the migration store.

segment.source: The encryption key or the text file that contains the encryption key.
segment.target: The encryption key or the text file that contains the encryption key.

segment.source: Include and exclude patterns for selective data extraction.
segment.target: Include and exclude patterns for selective data extraction.

segment.source: In addition, you can specify the file patterns that you want to extract by using the /i option to include file patterns or the /e option to exclude file patterns.
segment.target: In addition, you can specify the file patterns that you want to extract by using the /i option to include file patterns or the /e option to exclude file patterns.

segment.source: When both the /i option and the /e option are used in the same command, include patterns take precedence over exclude patterns.
segment.target: When both the /i option and the /e option are used in the same command, include patterns take precedence over exclude patterns.

segment.source: Note that this is different from the include and exclude rules used in the ScanState and LoadState tools.
segment.target: Note that this is different from the include and exclude rules used in the ScanState and LoadState tools.

segment.source: To run the USMTutils tool with the /extract option
segment.target: To run the USMTutils tool with the /extract option

segment.source: To extract files from the compressed migration store onto the destination computer, use the following USMTutils syntax:
segment.target: To extract files from the compressed migration store onto the destination computer, use the following USMTutils syntax:

segment.source: Cd /d USMTpath usmtutils /extract filePathdestinationPath/i:includePattern/e:excludePattern/l:logfile/decrypt:AlgID {/key:keystring | /keyfile:filename}/o
segment.target: Cd /d USMTpath usmtutils /extract filePathdestinationPath/i:includePattern/e:excludePattern/l:logfile/decrypt:AlgID {/key:keystring | /keyfile:filename}/o

segment.source: Where the placeholders have the following values:
segment.target: Where the placeholders have the following values:

segment.source: USMTpath is the location where you have saved the USMT files and tools.
segment.target: USMTpath is the location where you have saved the USMT files and tools.

segment.source: filePath is the location of the migration store.
segment.target: filePath is the location of the migration store.

segment.source: destination path is the location of the file where you want the /extract option to put the extracted migration store contents.
segment.target: destination path is the location of the file where you want the /extract option to put the extracted migration store contents.

segment.source: includePattern specifies the pattern for the files to include in the extraction.
segment.target: includePattern specifies the pattern for the files to include in the extraction.

segment.source: excludePattern specifies the pattern for the files to omit from the extraction.
segment.target: excludePattern specifies the pattern for the files to omit from the extraction.

segment.source: AlgID is the cryptographic algorithm that was used to create the migration store on the ScanState command line.
segment.target: AlgID is the cryptographic algorithm that was used to create the migration store on the ScanState command line.

segment.source: logfile is the location and name of the log file.
segment.target: logfile is the location and name of the log file.

segment.source: keystring is the encryption key that was used to encrypt the migration store.
segment.target: keystring is the encryption key that was used to encrypt the migration store.

segment.source: filename is the location and name of the text file that contains the encryption key.
segment.target: filename is the location and name of the text file that contains the encryption key.
